    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-08T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-08T07:00:00-05:00" n="548"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d548">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">561.35E1/62: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-08T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 8, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 8—8:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>108. From Atherton: Informal conferences began yesterday continuing late into
                    night developed that Chadbourne countries wanted dictum commitment that surplus
                    crops particularly in the Philippines would be disposed of in five annual
                    installments preferably in the United States.</p>
                <p>Pending instructions we have taken position that disposal of initial Philippine
                    surplus could be discussed with other exporting countries in the hopes of
                    reaching terms that might be satisfactory to the American Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
